# Typecraft Web – Project Overview

## Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19
- **Styling**: Panda CSS (styled-system); no Tailwind/CSS-in-JS
- **UI primitives**: Ark UI (`@ark-ui/react`)
- **Lint/format**: Biome (no ESLint/Prettier)
- **Tests**: Vitest, Testing Library, vitest-axe
- **Path alias**: `@/*` → `./src/*` (use for all src imports)

## Commands

- `pnpm dev` – dev server
- `pnpm build` – production build
- `pnpm lint` – Biome check
- `pnpm format` – Biome format
- `pnpm fix` – Biome check --write
- `pnpm test` / `pnpm test:run` / `pnpm test:coverage` – Vitest
- `pnpm prepare` – husky + `panda codegen` (run after clone / dependency
  changes)

## Folder structure

- `src/app/` – Next.js App Router (layout, page, routes)
- `src/components/` – core → shared → features
- `src/theme/` – Panda theme system (recipes, colors, semantic tokens, themes,
  conditions, keyframes)
- `docs/design-system/` – Design system documentation (semantic token contract,
  theme rules, migration guidelines)
- `src/hooks/`, `src/utils/`, `src/constants/`, `src/types/` – shared logic and
  types
- `src/__tests__/integration/` – integration tests
- `src/tests/vitest.setup.ts` – Vitest globals and mocks (e.g. Ark UI)

## Conventions

- Use **Biome** for formatting and linting; do not introduce ESLint/Prettier.
- Use **Panda** for all styling; do not add Tailwind or arbitrary CSS-in-JS.
- Use the **`@/`** path alias for imports under `src/`.
- Theme palettes live in `src/theme/colors/*` and semantic theme mappings live
  in `src/theme/themes/*`.
- Components and recipes must rely on semantic tokens (`fg.default`,
  `bg.default`, `border`, `accent.*`, `success`, `warning`, `error`, `typing.*`)
  instead of raw palette tokens.
- New recipes must be registered in `src/theme/recipes/index.ts` and Panda
  codegen should be run when theme or recipe definitions change.
